<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-02T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-02T08:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">765.94/55: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-02T22:00:00+09:00">November 2, 1937—10
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 2—10:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>514. 1. The evening papers report that the Cabinet today approved an
                        important diplomatic document which was then submitted to the Emperor for
                        approval; that after examination by the Privy Council and approval by the
                        Emperor the document will be signed.</p>
                    <p>2. The document under reference is believed to be a treaty with Italy to
                        combat communism probably with an additional secret clause.</p>
                    <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>